             <div style="margin-bottom:10px">
             <h2>Challenge No. 1 (7/8/2009)</h2>
             <h3>Build a #140HTML tweet aggregator</h3>
             <p>Create a web page or Twitter client that displays tweets tagged with <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=140HTML">#140HTML</a> and properly (and beautifully) interprets the HTML code contained within the tweets.</p>
             <p>$100 goes to the <strong style="background-color:#f48120;padding:0 5px;">first</strong> person or team who builds this reasonably well. This is a <em>speed</em> challenge. "Reasonably well" is defined by us, and at our discretion. Winner will be selected in 24 hours (7/9/2009 @ 3pm EST).</p>
             <p>You'll continue to own your code. We just want to see an #140HTML twitter client / aggregator out there.</p>
             <p>Submit your entries to <a href="http://twitter.com/dvlprs.com">@dvlprs</a> via Twitter or email <a href="mailto:hello@sawhorsemedia.com">hello@sawhorsemedia.com</a>.</p>
             <p><strong>Winner:</strong> @aaronfoss / <a href="http://www.nycfug.com/140HTML/">entry</a><br/>
             <strong>Runner up:</strong> @maxt3r / <a href="http://beta.fast-ideas.ru/">entry</a><br/>
             <strong>Runner up:</strong> @mrb_bk / <a href="http://the140html.heroku.com/">entry</a><br/></p>
             </div>
